11. Docker Compose (Multi-Service Systems)

Docker Compose lets you define and run multiple containers as a single application.

Example:

services:
  app:
    image: nginx
    ports:
      - "8080:80"

  redis:
    image: redis:7

docker compose up -d        # start all services in background
docker compose down         # stop and remove containers, network, etc.
docker compose ps           # list running compose services
docker compose logs         # view logs from all services
docker compose up -d --build # rebuild images and start services



12. Production Best Practices

docker run --restart unless-stopped nginx
# keeps the container running unless it is explicitly stopped (auto-restarts on crash or reboot)

Never use latest tag
nginx:latest   ❌
nginx:1.25     ✅

Define resource limits
with --cpus and --memory

Always use restart policies
--restart unless-stopped
| Policy         | Meaning                         |
| -------------- | ------------------------------- |
| no             | never restart                   |
| on-failure     | restart only if crash           |
| always         | always restart                  |
| unless-stopped | restart unless manually stopped |



Healthchecks
HEALTHCHECK CMD curl -f http://localhost || exit 1

States:
starting
healthy
unhealthy

