14. Real Production Incidents

CrashLoop Container

Cause:

bad config
missing environment variables
app exits immediately after start

🔍 How to debug

docker logs container
docker inspect container

🔧 Fix

correct config/env vars
rollback to previous stable image
fix startup command
---------------
Memory Crash (OOMKilled)

Cause

memory leak
no memory limits defined

Fix

increase memory limit
fix memory leak in application
---------------

Network Failure

Cause:
- DNS misconfiguration
- firewall / security rules blocking traffic

Fix:
- inspect container networking (docker network inspect / docker exec)
- verify DNS resolution (resolv.conf, ping service names)

15. Docker Exec & Runtime Debugging

docker exec -it container sh
# opens an interactive shell inside the running container (minimal environments usually use sh)

docker exec -it container bash
# opens a Bash shell inside the container (only works if bash is installed in the image)

docker exec container ls
# runs a single command inside the container without opening an interactive session

Environment variables
Print variables inside container
printenv

👉 shows all environment variables available at runtime

Set variables at runtime
docker run -e USERNAME=admin nginx

🧠 Meaning
-e injects environment variables into the container process
used for configuration without rebuilding images

Push image to registry
docker push localhost:5000/my-image

🧠 Important requirement

Before pushing, image must be tagged correctly:

docker tag my-image localhost:5000/my-image # localhost:5000 for local registry. my-image for repo inside registry








